  "prompt": "How can I remove certain questions/answers from my feed?",
  "response": "To remove certain questions or answers from your feed, you can use the \"Mute\" feature. Here's how:\n\n1. Find the question or answer you want to remove from your feed.\n2. Click on the three vertical dots at the top right of the post.\n3. Select \"Mute\" from the dropdown menu.\n\nOnce you've muted a question or answer, it will no longer appear in your feed. Note that muting a post won't delete it or prevent others from seeing it; it only affects your personal feed.\n\nIf you want to unmute a post later, you can do so by going to your profile, selecting \"Settings,\" then \"Mutings,\" and removing the post from the list.\n\nKeep in mind that the exact steps might vary slightly depending on the platform or app you're using. If you're having trouble finding the mute option, feel free to provide more details about the specific platform you're using, and I'll do my best to help.",
